                <h1>HB2 compromise signed into law, Duke responds</h1>
                
                                    <figure class="dom-art-container my-4">
                                                    <img src="https://snworksceo.imgix.net/dtc/0e97e6d6-5160-411b-9f66-ef5346fb3ad9.sized-1000x1000.jpg?w=1000" alt="&lt;p&gt;Gov.&#x20;Roy&#x20;Cooper&#x20;and&#x20;leaders&#x20;of&#x20;the&#x20;North&#x20;Carolina&#x20;General&#x20;Assembly&#x20;struck&#x20;a&#x20;&quot;compromise&quot;&#x20;measure&#x20;to&#x20;undo&#x20;portions&#x20;of&#x20;House&#x20;Bill&#x20;2.&amp;nbsp&#x3B;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;" class="w-100">
                                                <div class="domphoto-caption mt-2 text-left text-md-right">
                            <p>Gov. Roy Cooper and leaders of the North Carolina General Assembly struck a "compromise" measure to undo portions of House Bill 2.&nbsp;</p>

                                                             <aside class="photo-caption photo-credit d-block pl-1">
                                    <figcaption class="d-block">
                                                                                    Photo by <a href="https://www.dukechronicle.com/staff/picasa-2-0">Picasa 2.0</a> |
